---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Computer Vision Segmentation Demo - Ahmad Saladin"
  description="Placeholder PoC page for a computer vision segmentation walkthrough covering image input, mask output, overlays, post-processing, and deployment considerations."
  sideBarActiveItemID="pocs"
>
  <article class="prose max-w-3xl">
    <p class="not-prose text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-primary">Guided demo planned</p>
    <h1>Computer Vision Segmentation Demo</h1>
    <h2>What It Does</h2>
    <p>This PoC will provide a visual walkthrough of image input, segmentation mask, overlay result, post-processing, and deployment considerations.</p>
    <h2>Who It Is For</h2>
    <p>Teams building medical, beauty, industrial, or inspection-related image analysis workflows.</p>
    <h2>Demo Status</h2>
    <p>For v0, this is a placeholder or static walkthrough. It is not a live backend demo yet.</p>
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p>User -> Frontend -> API -> Preprocessing -> Model inference -> Post-processing -> Mask and overlay result</p>
    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>OpenCV, PyTorch, ONNX, segmentation, Python, FastAPI, object storage.</p>
    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <p>The v0 version does not upload images, run model inference, generate masks, or depend on a VPS/GPU backend.</p>
    <h2>Productionization Plan</h2>
    <p>Production work would add auth, monitoring, retries, error handling, rate limits, model evaluation, scaling, and cost controls.</p>
    <h2>CTA</h2>
    <p>Want to build something like this? <a href="/contact">Contact me</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
